{
  "texts": [
    "In both GPT-4o and Claude 3.5 Sonnet, the CoT and CoT-SC prompting techniques resulted in similar percentage scores, which were approximately 2.5 percent higher than the ZS prompting's scores.",
    "The error count of GPT-4o with ZS was approximately 25 higher than that observed for CoT and CoT-SC.",
    "However, the combination of Gemini with CoT or CoT-SC did not improve the accuracy but produced wider percentage scores across repeated measurements, with ranges of 1.9 and 1.2.",
    "The error count of Gemini with ZS was approximately 9 and 18 fewer than that observed for CoT and CoT-SC.",
    "Moreover, RAP obtained better scores (less error counts), compared to ZS, in GPT-4o; however it slightly decreased the performance of Claude and Gemini models."
  ]
}